      • initialiseState

        public void initialiseState(fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.time.Time initialTime)
        Description copied from interface: fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces.ModelI
        initialise the state of the model to make it ready to execute a simulation run.

        Description

        The standard predefined state initialisation will set the time to the next event. Hence, if a specific model has to perform some initialisations which the first internal transition depends upon, it must first perform them and then call the inherited method using super.

        Contract

         pre     initialTime != null
 pre     initialTime.greaterThanOrEqual(Time.zero(getSimulatedTimeUnit()))
 post    isInitialised()

      • output

        public java.util.ArrayList<fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.events.EventI> output()
        Description copied from interface: fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces.AtomicModelI
        maps the current internal state to the output set; this method is user-model-dependent hence must be implemented by the user for atomic models.

        Description

        Beware that when this method is called, though the simulation time has conceptually reached the time if the next internal event, the value returned by getCurrentStateTime has not yet been update to that time. Hence the actual current simulation time is given by this.getCurrentStateTime().add(this.getNextTimeAdvance()).

        Contract

         pre     isInitialised()
 pre     getNextTimeAdvance().lessThan(Duration.INFINITY)
 pre     getNextTimeAdvance().equals(getTimeOfNextEvent().subtract(getCurrentStateTime()))
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Returns:
        the corresponding external events or null if none.
        See Also:
        AtomicModelI.output()

      • userDefinedInternalTransition

        public void userDefinedInternalTransition(fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.time.Duration elapsedTime)
        Description copied from interface: fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces.ModelI
        perform an internal transition; this method is user model-dependent hence must be implemented by the user for atomic models; the user implementation should not change any of the implementation related variables.

        Description

        The current simulation time when this method is called can be accessed by calling the method getCurrentStateTime.

        Contract

         pre     isInitialised()
 pre     getCurrentStateTime().equals(getTimeOfNextEvent())
 pre     elapsedTime != null
 pre     elapsedTime.greaterThanOrEqual(Duration.zero(getSimulatedTimeUnit()))
 pre     elapsedTime.lessThan(Duration.INFINITY)
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Specified by:
